    "4013409": {
        "Desc": "Talk to Chevreuse",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "All clear. Let's go."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Wait wait wait... Paimon's a little nervous now that we know he could be the killer. Can we go over our plan of action again?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "I'll go knock on the door, and make sure it's safe inside. Once we're sure that we're in the clear, I'll ask him to come with us for a quick round of questioning at the Gardes' headquarters."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "But can't we just arrest him?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "We still have no evidence that he's the killer, or that he lent the killer any direct aid."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Still, it would be appreciated if you could pick a Rainbow Rose from his garden for me while I'm talking to him. It will help the Marechaussee Phantom confirm Emilie's theory."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Sure, no problem! Just be careful, Chevreuse."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
    "4013404": {
        "Desc": "Go to the writer's home",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Ugh... Paimon's exhausted. Paimon definitely didn't expect having to float this far after a full day of filming..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "So, Chevreuse, why did you take us here?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "Did you find a new clue?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Affirmative. It wasn't anything conclusive, but it should show us a clear way forward."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Have you ever heard of someone by the name of Emilie?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Oh, you mean that famous perfumer?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "She's a good friend of mine. She's lent me her aid several times in the past to resolve some difficult cases."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "After I discovered the Rainbow Rose at the scene of the murder, I sent it to her. After all, she's probably the foremost expert on flowers and scents in all of Fontaine."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "And then...?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "There was nothing remarkable about the flower, or the trace amounts of soil left on it."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "But according to Emilie, the Rainbow Rose left by the killer was derived from a very rare cultivar."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Huh, Paimon didn't know that there were different varieties of Rainbow Rose! Paimon just thought that they grew everywhere in the wild..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Flowers that are deliberately cultivated will always show some different features from those that bloom in the wild."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "We already knew that the rose left at the scene belonged to a special cultivar, but with Emilie's expertise, we were able to pinpoint the place where it was first picked from."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Ohh! Paimon gets it now. So whoever first planted that Rainbow Rose was probably the killer!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Precisely. And after we checked what we learned against some sales records from the past, we discovered that there's only one person in all of Fontaine who could grow and sell this specific cultivar."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Huh, really? And who is it?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "It's the novelist."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "But didn't you say that he had an alibi?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "To be clear, I haven't changed my mind about him. I still don't think he was the one who pulled the trigger."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "However, that doesn't mean that the true culprit never visited him at his home, or never purchased a Rainbow Rose from his garden."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Whatever the case, we will have to confirm a number of things with him."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "So you mean, the next place we need to go is..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Chevreuse",
                    "T": "Yes, we're going to pay him a visit at his home."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
